\subsection{Shapechanger}
d821 11
a831 2
\subsubsection{A shapechanger is a separate genetic strain of human,
with the ability to change into the form of a particular animal.}
d833 1
a833 11
\textbf{Type:}
The player must roll D10 to determine what type of shape-changer their
character will be.

\begin{tabularx}{\linewidth}{Xl}
\textbf{Dice Roll}	& \textbf{Type} \\
1 -- 4			& Wolf \\
5 -- 6			& Tiger \\
7 -- 8			& Bear \\
9 -- 10			& Boar \\
\end{tabularx}
d835 5
a839 19
\textbf{Traits:} Shapechangers are identical in appearance to humans
when not in animal form.  Shapechangers are somewhat bestial in
nature, adopting traits one might expect from an anthropomorphised
wolf, tiger, bear or boar.  There exists a love/hate relationship
between humans and shapechangers: shapechangers possess some degree of
animal magnetism, but, if discovered, can expect severe treatment at
the hands of humans.  Shapechangers are, on the whole, bitter towards
humans, and are not above using humans to their advantage.  There are
very few ways to tell a shapechanger from a human (e.g., they will be
discomforted by garlic) and these vary by shapechanger type.
Shapechangers are a ruthless lot.

\textbf{Special Abilities:}
\begin{enumerate}
\setlength\itemsep{0pt}
