\subsubsection{The character's order of birth modifies their initial
allotment of experience and monies.}
d1274 6
a1279 18
A bastard was born under dubious circumstances, but should be able to
prove who is their less-favoured parent.  They will have had to fend
for themself at an early age, and can handle themself better than
most.  A bastard receives 50\% of the money due them, but begins with
25\% more Experience Points.

A legitimate child is the offspring of a couple in wedlock at the time
of their birth.  Such a child will be the second or younger of the
acknowledged children.  Their parents gave them as much attention as
they could.  A legitimate child's monies and experience are unmodified
by their order of birth.

A first child is the first legitimate child born to their parents
(though others less fortunate than them may have arrived earlier).
They have received better treatment than their siblings, but have been
shielded a little from some of the harsher realities of life.  A first
child receives a 50\% increase to their initial monies, but a 25\%
decrease to their starting Experience Point total.
d1281 3
a1283 2
