\subsubsection{A player should choose their character's height and weight.}
d1488 6
a1493 26
The character's height and weight should be chosen according to the
player's idea of the character, with due regard to the character's
primary characteristics, race and background.  The following chart
will give an idea of reasonable values for each attribute.  Included
is a percentile distribution both to indicate the likelihood of a
person being a particular height, and also to allow the height to be
generated randomly.

\begin{tabular}{cccc}
\textbf{Dice} & \textbf{Factor} & \textbf{Weight} & \textbf{Range} \\
01	& 1	& 128	& 98-180 \\
02	& 2	& 130	& 100-180 \\
03--04	& 3	& 135	& 108-180 \\
05--09	& 4	& 140	& 111-187 \\
10--17	& 5	& 145	& 114-190 \\
18--27	& 6	& 150	& 116-192 \\
28--40	& 7	& 155	& 121-197 \\
41--54	& 8	& 158	& 124-200 \\
55--70	& 9	& 160	& 129-213 \\
71--82	& 10	& 165	& 133-214 \\
83--89	& 11	& 170	& 138-228 \\
90--95	& 12	& 176	& 140-230 \\
96--98	& 13	& 184	& 140-240 \\
99	& 14	& 191	& 140-250 \\
00	& 15	& 197	& 140-260 \\
\end{tabular}
d1495 1
a1495 21
The \emph{Factor} should be added to the base height determined from
the following table based on the character's race and gender.  This
gives the character's height in inches.

The \emph{Weight} gives the average weight in Pounds for this height
factor.  This value is modified by the modifier given in the following
table.

The \emph{Range} gives the range between which 90\% of people of the
given height factor fall.

\begin{tabular}{@@{}l@@{\hspace{0.5em}}c@@{\hspace{0.5em}}c@@{\hspace{0.5em}}c@@{\hspace{0.5em}}c@@{}}
\textbf{Race} & \textbf{Male} & \textbf{Mod} &\textbf{Female} & \textbf{Mod} \\
Dwarf		& 40	& 0.6	& 38	& 0.5 \\
Elf		& 64	& 0.8	& 60	& 0.65 \\
Giant		& 100	& 3.0	& 96	& 2.5 \\
Halfling	& 30	& 0.3	& 28	& 0.3 \\
Human		& 62	& 1.0	& 57	& 0.8 \\
Orc		& 60	& 1.1	& 54	& 0.9 \\
Shapechanger	& 62	& 1.0	& 57	& 0.8 \\
\end{tabular}
d1497 5
a1501 2
The \emph{Modifier} is the number by which the weight and range values
in the above table should be multiplied.
