characteristics) concerning their character.  A model Character
Record, on which all pertinent information can be recorded, is
provided within this rulebook.  The GM can choose to use a different
recording form, or modify the one provided.  Whichever the case, the
GM must be provided with a complete and current character record for
each player's character.  The GM can then verify the information on
each record, or make corrections where necessary.  Each player should
also have a copy of their own character's record, though as play goes
on, the two records will differ (the GM may note something about a
character which the player does not know, such as a curse).  In
addition to a character record, a player must maintain a notebook for
recording all monetary and EP expenditure.  This should be checked by
the GM at the beginning of every adventure and ``signed off'' by the
GM when satisfied that all calculations are correct with respect to
money, time and EP.
